        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="915" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d915">
                <head>Government of the Canton of Basel Town</head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Basel</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-06">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 6, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Mayor and council of the canton of Basel-Stadt to the
                            Bundesrath, in Berne</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: We learn from the public papers that
                        your supreme authorities have voted an address of sympathy and condolence to
                        the United States, on account of the death of their worthy President, at a
                        time when long-desired peace was just taking the place of a terrible
                        war.</p>
                <p>We presume the address is in the name of all the cantons, and we are thankful
                        for the opportunity of adding our names to it. But if we are mistaken, we
                        suggest that a circular be promulged for the purpose, that each canton may
                        know what to do.</p>
                <p>We commend you to the protection of Divine Providence, and subscribe
                        ourselves,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>C. STCHLIN, <hi rend="italic">Mayor</hi>
                            </item>
                            <item>DR. BISCONOFF, <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
